esign'''\n\n===Lifetime Achievement Awards===\n* '''[[Julie Andrews]]'''\n* '''[[Olivia de Havilland]]'''\n* '''[[Roger Corman]]'''\n* '''[[Martin Scorsese]]'''\n* '''[[John Waters]]'''\n\n===Special Achievement Awards===\n* Agencia Nacional de Cinema (Brazil) for supporting art against the attacks from a fascist government.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Online Film Critics Society Awards}}\n\n[[Category:2016 film awards]]\n[[Category:Online Film Critics Society Awards|2016]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 23\n| award            = Online Film Critics Society Awards\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| date             = \n| site             = \n| host             = \n| preshow          = \n| producer         = \n| director         = \n| best_picture     = ''[[Parasite (2019 film)|Parasite]]''\n| most_wins        = ''Parasite'' (6)\n| network          = \n| most_nominations = ''[[Once Upon a Time in Hollywood|Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood]]'' (7)\n| duration         = \n| ratings          = \n| last             = [[Online Film Critics Society Awards 2018|22nd]]\n| next             = [[Online Film Critics Society Awards 2020|24th]]\n}}\n\nThe '''23rd [[Online Film Critics Society Awards]]''', honoring the best in film for 2019, were announced on January 6, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ofcs.org/awards/2019-awards-23rd-annual/|title=2019 Awards Winners (23rd Annual)|date=January 6, 2020|accessdate=February 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width: 50%\" | [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width: 50%\" | [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n# '''''[[Parasite (2019 film)|Parasite]]'''''\n# ''[[The Irishman]]''\n# ''[[Once Upon a Time in Hollywood|Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood]]''\n# ''[[Marr